  "texts": [
    "We present our measurements of ingroup solidarity and outgroup hostility across four conditions in Fig. 1.",
    "These include (1) responses from models using the default prompt (Fig. 1a), (2) responses from outlier models using the default prompt (Fig.",
    "1b), (3) responses from instruction-tuned and preference-tuned models using the instruction prompt (Fig. 1c) and (4) measurements from human-written text in pretraining corpora that serve as our baseline (Fig.",
    "We used the same regression procedure for the pretraining data from each corpus and overall by randomly downsampling to 2,000 sentences per corpus per sentence group.",
    "We also estimated overall ingroup-solidarity and outgroup-hostility values using mixed-effects logistic regressions with the same fixed effects and model names as the random intercept."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}